==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Chaffinch
<hw>Chaf"finch</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Chiff-chaff</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A bird of Europe
(<spn>Fringilla c⟦oe⟧lebs</spn>), having a variety of very sweet songs,
and highly valued as a cage bird; -- called also <altname>copper
finch</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chaffing</ent>⟦br⟧
